<% content_for :title, "Installation" %>

<%= h2_with_anchor "Overview" %>

<p>Launch10 consists of two main components that work together:</p>
<br />

<ol>
  <li>The Rails repo (built off Jumpstart Pro + Inertia Rails frontend)</li>
  <li>The Langgraph repo (builds the landing pages, SEO plans, and deployments)</li>
</ol>

<%= h2_with_anchor "Architecture Overview" %>

<p>Rails handles signups, payments, authentication, and user management. Langgraph handles all AI-driven operations for Launch10.</p>

<div class="not-prose">
  <pre><code>Rails Frontend (JWT Auth) → Langgraph API → Database
                                    ↓
                              WebContainers
                                    ↓
                              Live Preview</code></pre>
</div>

<%= h2_with_anchor "Installation" %>

<%= h3_with_anchor "Rails Installation" %>

<pre><code>
cd rails_app
cp .env.example .env # Make any necessary changes to .env
bundle install
bundle exec rake db:create db:migrate db:seed
</code></pre>

<%= h3_with_anchor "Langgraph Installation" %>

<pre><code>
cd langgraph_app
pnpm install
cp .env.example .env # Make any necessary changes to .env
</code></pre>

<%= h2_with_anchor "Running Dev Environment" %>

<%= h3_with_anchor "Rails Frontend" %>

<pre><code>
cd rails_app
bin/dev
</code></pre>

<%= h3_with_anchor "Rails Backend" %>

<pre><code>
cd rails_app
bundle exec rails s
</code></pre>

<%= h3_with_anchor "Langgraph Backend" %>

<pre><code>
cd langgraph_app
langdev dev
</code></pre>

